# Tizen Protocol Reference

## Connection
- WebSocket: `wss://<host>:8002/api/v2/channels/samsung.remote.control?name=<base64_name>&token=<token>`
- REST API: `http://<host>:8001/api/v2/`
- TV uses a self-signed cert → `ssl=False` in aiohttp

## Token pairing
1. Connect WS without token (or with expired token)
2. TV shows "Allow / Deny" dialog
3. After user allows: TV sends `ms.channel.connect` with token in `data.clients[*].attributes.token`
4. Save token to config entry immediately (rotation / preservation)
5. On next connect: include `&token=<saved_token>` — no dialog shown

## Power FSM (5 states)
```
OFF → WAKING_UP → ON → TURNING_OFF → OFF
WAKING_UP → UNAUTHORIZED → (retry) → WAKING_UP
```
- OFF: slow poll every 20s (GET :8001/api/v2/)
- WAKING_UP: fast poll every 1s, give up after 30s
- ON: liveness probe every 20s (GET :8001/api/v2/)
- TURNING_OFF: optimistic; forced to OFF after 20s
- UNAUTHORIZED: retry after 30s

## Key sending
- Method: `ms.remote.control` with `Cmd=Click`, `DataOfCmd=<KEY_NAME>`
- Queue with 120ms inter-key delay (KeySender)
- Keys only sent when `power_state == ON`

## App management
- Discovery: `ed.installedApp.get` WS message (requires `has_ghost_api` cap)
- Launch downloaded apps (app_type 2): REST POST `/api/v2/applications/{appId}`
- Launch native apps (app_type 4): WS `ed.apps.launch` with `action_type=DEEP_LINK`
- `org.tizen.browser` is always native (WS launch) regardless of `app_type`
- Current-app detection: REST GET `/api/v2/applications/{appId}` → `{"running": true}`
  (requires `meta_tag_nav` cap)

## TV generation / capability detection
Model string from `GET /api/v2/` → `device.modelName`:
- `16_HAWKM_FHD` → old generation; no `meta_tag_nav`, no `has_ghost_api`
- `17_*`, `18_*` → transitional; partial caps
- `QE49Q67RATXXH` (no numeric prefix) → modern; full caps

## WOL
- Send 5 WOL magic packets, 120ms apart, before entering WAKING_UP
- MAC from `device.wifiMac` in /api/v2/ response (saved to config entry)

## Key name convention
Keys follow Samsung convention: `KEY_VOLUMEUP`, `KEY_MUTE`, `KEY_HOME`, `KEY_ENTER`, etc.
Full list in `const.py`. The TV accepts any string; only well-known names are listed there.
